# Raven Design System

Published Storybook: https://69c7a797c64a933a5e31fccf-frcosnnnzo.chromatic.com/?path=/docs/components-all-components--docs

## How to Use

- Before building any UI, check the Storybook for existing components, patterns, and tokens.
- Browse by category: Inputs, Data Display, Feedback, Surfaces, Navigation, Layout.
- Each component page includes variants, sizes, colors, states, and real-world Raven product patterns.

## Theme

Wrap the app with `ravenNearMissTheme` from the design system. All styling flows from the theme automatically.

| Token         | Value                          |
|---------------|--------------------------------|
| Primary       | `#4A148C` (deep purple)        |
| Primary Light | `#CE93D8`                      |
| Primary Dark  | `#311B92`                      |
| Font          | Source Sans 3                  |
| Button radius | 50px (pill)                    |
| Card radius   | 24px                           |
| Input radius  | 8px                            |
| Icon style    | Rounded only (`@mui/icons-material/*Rounded`) |
| Button text   | UPPERCASE                      |

## Component Usage

```tsx
import { ThemeProvider } from '@mui/material/styles';
import { ravenNearMissTheme } from '@raven-ui/theme/ravenNearMissTheme';
import Button from '@mui/material/Button';
import DeleteRounded from '@mui/icons-material/DeleteRounded';

<ThemeProvider theme={ravenNearMissTheme}>
  <Button variant="contained" startIcon={<DeleteRounded />}>
    Delete
  </Button>
</ThemeProvider>
```

## Rules

1. Always use **Rounded** icon variants — never use default/filled/outlined/sharp.
2. Use `sx` prop with theme tokens (`primary.main`, `text.secondary`, `background.paper`) — never hard-code hex colors.
3. Use Typography `variant` prop (`h5`, `body1`, `body1Bold`, `caption`) — never set font sizes directly.
4. Use the theme's elevation via `contained` buttons — do not override `boxShadow` manually.
5. Check the Storybook's "Raven Product Patterns" story on each component for domain-specific examples before inventing new patterns.
